HEADWORD: Despoina
<hw>Despoina</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <fld>(Classical Mythology)</fld>
<def>the daughter of <person>Zeus</person> and <person>Demeter</person>;
made queen of the underworld by <person>Pluto</person> in ancient
mythology; identified with Roman
<altname>Proserpina</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Persephone, Kore, Cora.</syn>⟦br⟧
